    <h2>About Hisashi Murayama</h2>
 

  <p>Hisashi Murayama was born in Japan on 12th December, 1973. After completing a bachelor degree at  Kansai University of Foreign Studies - Language Spanish major - he moved to NY. He studied at the International Center of Photography between 1998 and 1999. Since year 2000, he has travelled between New York and most of Western Europe. Hisashi lived in Madrid during 2002, where he participated in a group exhibition at PHOTO ESPANA, and an exhibition in Japan. Through the years, he has participated regularly in Recontres Internationales de la Photographie, Arles � either individually or as a member of the independent international photographers group Tangophoto. Other exhibitions include Visapourlimage in Perpignan, France, and Fotofiesta Medellin in Colombia.</p>

<p>Currently Hisashi is in NY and preparing for a group show at  Fnac Photogallery and Festival of Light, Buenos Aires, Argentina for 2004.<br />
